# Neko Flow — example modes and substates.
# Copy to ~/.config/neko-flow/flow_modes.txt and edit.
#
# Super+Alt+Left/Right  — cycle modes
# Super+Alt+Up/Down     — cycle substates
# Super+Alt+Return      — mark substate active + open mode note
#
# Substate line:  - Label - description [ButtonId]
# Headers:        @ROUTINE @TASKS @INLINE @DESC

[COMMS]
@DESC Triage inboxes and messages before deep work.
@ROUTINE Routine
- Team Slack - Check mentions and threads [SlackMain]
- Email - Triage inbox [GmailInbox]
- Notes - Update notes below

[WORK]
@DESC Focused work on current projects.
@ROUTINE Routine
- Deep work - One task, no context switching
- Project board - Review tasks [ProjectBoard]
- Notes - Update notes below

[CLEAN]
@DESC Clear digital and physical clutter.
@ROUTINE Routine
- Clean Mail [GmailInbox]
- Clean Desktop [Desktop]
- Clean Downloads [Downloads]
- Clean GDrive [GDrive]

[CREATE]
@DESC Prototype, build, polish side projects.
@ROUTINE Routine
- Notes - Capture ideas below

@TASKS Tasks
